```python
from math import comb

def find_subset_of_length_n(set_of_elements):
    return comb(len(set_of_elements), 327)
```
This function calculates the number of all subsets of length 327 from given set of elements using combination formula from mathematics (nCr = n!/(r!(n-r)!)). The comb function in python's math library computes the number of ways to choose k items from n items without repetition and without order. It uses the formula n! / (k! * (n - k)!) to calculate the number of subsets.
This will throw an error if len(set_of_elements) is less than 327 as it is not possible to choose 327 elements from a set that contains less than 327 elements.
